\begin_layout Standard
Another protocol attempts to use the light from lasers to displace the basilar
 membrane.
 In order for this to be successful, it may be necessary to place metallic
 mirrors with high reflectance in order to increase momentum transfer from
 incoming photons.
 Though beads would be another option, these may increase the load to the
 basilar membrane, thus decreasing accuracy of forthcoming data.
 A protocol has been designed previously for the fabrication of gold mirrors,
 with variations in the protocol in order to create disks within the range
 desired for optical displacement of the basilar membrane.
\end_layout

