 This solution was incubated at 90C for 30 minutes.
 Additionally, the salicylic acid solution was prepared as before and filtered.
 This solution was heated to 90C, and 7 ml of the salicylic acid solution
 was added dropwise to the incubated gold chloride solution over a course
 of 60 seconds.
 The combined solution was then filtered once more and incubated at 90C
 for 30 minutes.
 After incubation, the solution was sealed with Parafilm and stored at room
 temperature in a dark location away from mechanical disturbances.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unlike the previous attempt, this solution had a gold tint as opposed to
 a purple hue.
 
\end_layout

