\begin_inset Formula $HAuCl_{4}\cdot3H_{2}O$
\end_inset

) - 250 ml beaker (#1395); 0.3 g / 40 ml, where M=393.8g
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
This solution was then filtered and brought to pH 2.42 with 350 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu l$
\end_inset

 of 1M HCl.
 The solution was subsequently incubated at 90C for 30 minutes.
 After incubation, 50 ml of 4% paraformaldehyde was added to the solution.
 This was then incubated at 90C for 2 hours.
 The final solution was then placed in a dish, covered (but not sealed),
 and stored at room temperature in a dark location away from mechanical
 disturbances.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The solution in this experiment was a dark yellow, less transparent than
 that in 
